Hi Alex,

You might have more luck with this question on the ant-user mailing list.

You don&#39;t include detail of the actual &quot;emit.event&quot; target, and that&#39;s 
where you would need to make changes. I assume from your description 
that it makes use of the &lt;exec&gt; Ant task.

If ${message.text} has spaces in it but you want it treated as a single 
param on the command line, you can use a nested &lt;ant value=&quot;&quot;&gt;:

&lt;exec executable=&quot;emit_event&quot;&gt;
  &lt;arg value=&quot;-msg&quot;/&gt;
  &lt;arg value=&quot;${message.text}&quot;/&gt;
&lt;/exec&gt;

See http://ant.apache.org/manual/using.html#arg for more info.

